    <detaileddescription>
<para>This weight is computed as <formula id="4">$w = \frac{d_2^a A_0 - d^a B + d_0^a A_2}{A_0 A_2}$</formula> with notations shown in the figure below and <formula id="1">$a$</formula> any real number being the power parameter.</para>
<para>Here, <computeroutput>q</computeroutput> is a query point and the points <computeroutput>p0</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>p1</computeroutput>, and <computeroutput>p2</computeroutput> are its neighbors.</para>
<para>This weight supports only planar configurations (see more in section about <ref refid="index_1Weights_Implementation_Coplanarity" kindref="member">Coplanarity</ref>) while alternative formulations are explained in <ref refid="index_1Weights_Implementation" kindref="member">Implementation</ref>.</para>
<para><anchor id="group__PkgWeightsRefThreePointFamilyWeights_1fig__three_point_family_weight"/> <image type="html" name="three_point_family.svg"></image>
 <image type="latex" name="three_point_family.svg" width="15cm"></image>
 <htmlonly block="yes"> &lt;div class=&quot;cgal_figure_caption&quot;&gt; </htmlonly>  <ref refid="group__PkgWeightsRefThreePointFamilyWeights_1fig__three_point_family_weight" kindref="member">fig__three_point_family_weight</ref> Notation used for the three point family weight. <htmlonly block="yes"> &lt;/div&gt; </htmlonly> <linebreak/>
</para>
<para><bold>Specializations</bold><linebreak/>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>For <formula id="5">$a = 0$</formula>, this weight is equal to the <ref refid="group__PkgWeightsRefWachspressWeights" kindref="compound">Wachspress Weight</ref> and <ref refid="group__PkgWeightsRefAuthalicWeights" kindref="compound">Authalic Weight</ref>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>For <formula id="2">$a = 1$</formula>, this weight is equal to the <ref refid="group__PkgWeightsRefMeanValueWeights" kindref="compound">Mean Value Weight</ref> and <ref refid="group__PkgWeightsRefTangentWeights" kindref="compound">Tangent Weight</ref>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>For <formula id="6">$a = 2$</formula>, this weight is equal to the <ref refid="group__PkgWeightsRefDiscreteHarmonicWeights" kindref="compound">Discrete Harmonic Weight</ref> and <ref refid="group__PkgWeightsRefCotangentWeights" kindref="compound">Cotangent Weight</ref>.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>GeomTraits</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>a model of <computeroutput><ref refid="classAnalyticWeightTraits__2" kindref="compound">AnalyticWeightTraits_2</ref></computeroutput> for 2D points; a model of <computeroutput><ref refid="classAnalyticWeightTraits__3" kindref="compound">AnalyticWeightTraits_3</ref></computeroutput> for 3D points</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="pre"><para>A1 != 0 &amp;&amp; A2 != 0 </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
